bug.short_desc: MenuButton interaction causes some parts of browser document to go black

long_desc.thetext: Following an upgrade from Qooxdoo 0.8.2 to Qooxdoo 1.0, MenuButtons are now exhibiting strange display behaviour in IE6, IE7 and IE8 (compatibility mode). This behaviour can also be seen in the menu demo. On the demo site http://demo.qooxdoo.org/current/demobrowser/#widget~Menu.html If you click the menu button, select a different option in the options sub menu, then click the menu button again, some of the browser display goes black as shown in the following screenshot. The link to the newsgroup post shows a screenshot of this issue This issue is currently blocking development and test activities. Our only possible workaround at the moment is to downgrade to Qooxdoo 0.8.2 (or possibly 0.8.3) depending on when this issue occurred.
Created attachment 702 Screenshot of the issue
I've also tested this in the 0.8.3 demo page and it works correctly. This issue appears to have been introduced between 0.8.3 and 1.0.
Thanks for the report. This is already fixed in trunk with Revision #21306 and will be incorporated in the upcoming 1.0.1 release which is targeted for this week.
Fix in trunk solves the problem
